                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d638">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">784A.02/7–1353:Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 638<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to <gloss
                            type="to">Rabbi Abba Hillel Silver</gloss>, at Cape Vincent, New
                        York</hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d638fn1">Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_DJF2"
                            >Dulles</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_BHA1"
                        >Byroade</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1953-07-13T17:44:00-04:00"
                            >July 13, 1953—5:44 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I had tried to reach you Saturday at President’s request to see if we could
                    concert any measures to halt abrupt transfer yesterday of Israel Foreign Office
                    from Tel Aviv to Jerusalem and thus obviate unfortunate repercussions in Middle
                    East and elsewhere.</p>
                <p>Unfortunately could not reach you and action has been taken. I have now stated
                    that the U.S. did not plan to move its Embassy to Jerusalem, feeling that this
                    would be inconsistent with outstanding U.N. Resolutions.</p>
                <p>Regret we could not get talking connection over telephone. Best regards.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DJF2">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">John Foster Dulles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
